\DOC curry

\TYPE {curry : (('a * 'b) -> 'c) -> 'a -> 'b -> 'c}

\SYNOPSIS
Converts a function on a pair to a corresponding curried function.

\DESCRIBE
The application {curry f} returns {\x y. f(x,y)}, so that
{
   curry f x y = f(x,y)
}
\FAILURE
Never fails.

\EXAMPLE
{
- val increment = curry op+ 1;
> val it = increment = fn : int -> int

- increment 6;
> val it = 7 : int
}
\SEEALSO
uncurry.

\ENDDOC
